         "description": "In the method getCorrelationStandardErrors(), the calculation of the standard error is incorrect. It should be ((1 - r^2) / (n - 2))^(1/2) instead of ((1 - r^2) / (n - 2))",
         "severity": "major",
         "location": {
            "file": "PearsonsCorrelation.java",
            "method": "getCorrelationStandardErrors",
            "line": 123
         }
      },
      {
         "description": "In the constructor PearsonsCorrelation(RealMatrix matrix), the method checkSufficientData(matrix) is called but its implementation is not shown. It is assumed that this method checks if the matrix has at least two rows and two columns. However, this assumption may be incorrect.",
         "severity": "minor",
         "location": {
            "file": "PearsonsCorrelation.java",
            "method": "PearsonsCorrelation",
            "line": 74
         }
      },
      {
         "description": "In the constructor PearsonsCorrelation(Covariance covariance), the covariance matrix is checked for null but the covariance instance is not checked for null. This may lead to a NullPointerException if the covariance instance is null.",
         "severity": "minor",
         "location": {
            "file": "PearsonsCorrelation.java",
            "method": "PearsonsCorrelation",
            "line": 106
         }
      },
      {
         "description": "In the constructor PearsonsCorrelation(RealMatrix covarianceMatrix, int numberOfObservations), the number of observations is not checked for validity. If the number of observations is less than 2, the correlation matrix will be invalid.",
         "severity": "minor",
         "location": {
            "file": "PearsonsCorrelation.java",
            "method": "PearsonsCorrelation",
